Class StackImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractStack
      • StackImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Stack

    public class StackImpl
extends AbstractStack
    An implementation of a stack that uses a as the underlying data structure. Not all operations on a stack will always be successful. For example, a programmer may try to pop an element from an empty stack. Since we hace not covered exceptions yet, we need another mechanism to report errors. In order to do that, methods of this list will return a ReturnObject that will contain either an object or an error value of the right kind (as defined in ErrorMessage).
